{"title":"Say Hello to the Deploy and Dissent, Ride Concepts’ First Ever MTB Helmets","link":"https://bikerumor.com/say-hello-to-the-deploy-and-dissent-ride-concepts-first-ever-mtb-helmets/","date":1747932364000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" alt=\"(Photos / Ride Concepts)\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://rideconcepts.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Ride Concepts</a>, a brand that has always been known for its MTB shoe offerings, now has its first two MTB helmets. Meet the <a href=\"https://rideconcepts.com/products/deploy-mips\" target=\"_blank\">Deploy</a> and the <a href=\"https://rideconcepts.com/products/dissent-mips\" target=\"_blank\">Dissent</a>, two all-new half-shell helmets made with the same passion, precision, and quality as their shoes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets Dissent first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-first-pic-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Dissent</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets Deploy first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Deploy-first-pic-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Deploy</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It doesn’t matter what type of trails you’re riding, Ride Concepts says that “<em>these helmets deliver premium protection, bold style, and rider-first comfort</em>“. Furthermore, they’re also supposed to be lightweight, full-featured, and ready to “send”.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s check ’em out!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Deploy – Built for the Long Haul, Ready for the Hot Lap</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets delpoy mips bro\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-mips-bro-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption> (All photos / Ride Concepts)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Ride Concepts Deploy helmet is said to be both lightweight and well-vented, without compromising on protection. It’s a helmet engineered for XC and Trail riders. In other words, riders who put in honkin’ miles while being confident when the trail gets techy.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets delpoy toungue in cheek\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-delpoy-toungue-in-cheek-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It rocks a classic polycarbonate shell in-molded over an EPS core with extended lower hard-body coverage. This increases durability, while a MIPS Evolve Core rotational management system provides new-tech crash protection. The Deploy uses a finely-tuned Flow-thru ventilation solution with 16 vents to keep airflow high and head temps low.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ride Concepts thinks the perfect customer for this helmet is the rider who “<em>chases singletrack miles, backcountry loops, or daily trail therapy. Ideal for sub-140mm travel bikes</em>“.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Deploy Tech Details &amp; Retail Pricing</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets deploy blurry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-blurry-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $140 / 140€</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Flow-thru ventilation with 16 large intake and exhaust ports</li>\n\n\n\n<li>In-mold EPS construction with full polycarbonate coverage</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Full lower hard-body shell for added durability and protection</li>\n\n\n\n<li>MIPS Evolve Core system to manage rotational energy in a crash</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Multi-position indexing visor with secure goggle stow</li>\n\n\n\n<li>FS2 micro-adjust fit system for a customizable dialed-in fit</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Premium moisture-wicking padding and reflective webbing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CPSC-certified</li>\n\n\n\n<li>three sizes (S 53-56cm, M 56-59cm &amp; L 59-62cm)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>claimed 400g (size M)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Dissent – Enduro’s New Enforcer </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets Dissent side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-Dissent-side-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dissent is a mountain bike helmet geared to protect you on more aggressive terrain. It’s Ride Concepts’ new lightweight, high-performance open-face helmet for enduro, all-mountain, and gravity riders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dissent is overbuilt on purpose, in the best way possible. It sports a tough 4-piece shell that utilizes extended polycarbonate coverage. It also has oversized venting, as well as goggle-friendly features. These could make it your go-to for easy summer park laps, race day, and every descent in between – that is, whenever you don’t need the extra protection of a full-face.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets dissent shralp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-shralp-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dissent uses MIPS Evolve Core as well to protect against rotational forces during an impact. The FS6 integrated fit system offers a locked-in feel, but is fine-tunable on the fly. Add a Fidlock magnetic buckle, X-Static anti-odor padding, and a burly adjustable Link visor mount, and you’ve got a helmet that’s as ready as you are.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-dune-e1747873124183.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"777\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-dune-e1747873124183.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets dissent dune\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-dune-e1747873124183.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-dune-e1747873124183-297x180.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-dune-e1747873124183-120x73.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-dune-e1747873124183-768x466.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Dune</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-black-e1747873139877.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"836\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-black-e1747873139877.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets dissent black\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-black-e1747873139877.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-black-e1747873139877-297x194.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-black-e1747873139877-120x78.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-black-e1747873139877-768x502.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Black</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-green-e1747873156453.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"762\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-green-e1747873156453.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets deploy green\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-green-e1747873156453.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-green-e1747873156453-297x177.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-green-e1747873156453-120x71.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-deploy-green-e1747873156453-768x457.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Green</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ride Concepts thinks the perfect customer for this helmet is the rider who “<em>pushes hard through chunky lines, race stages, and lift-served chaos. Ideal for bikes with over 140mm travel</em>“.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-white-e1747873107634.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"836\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-white-e1747873107634.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets dissent white\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-white-e1747873107634.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-white-e1747873107634-297x194.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-white-e1747873107634-120x78.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-white-e1747873107634-768x502.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>White</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Dissent Tech Details &amp; Retail Pricing</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners.webp\" alt=\"Ride Concepts New Helmets dissent corners\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ride-Concepts-New-Helmets-dissent-corners-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $190 / 190€</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Lightweight, durable 4-piece PC shell with in-mold EPS and oversized venting</li>\n\n\n\n<li>15 massive vents with internal airflow channeling</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Full lower hard-body polycarbonate coverage</li>\n\n\n\n<li>MIPS Evolve Core rotational energy management</li>\n\n\n\n<li>FS6 shell-integrated micro-adjust fit system</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fidlock magnetic snap buckle for quick, secure closure</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Quick-release strap adjusters and reflective polyester webbing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>X-Static®XT2 comfort pads with permanent anti-odor silver thread</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Multi-position visor with goggle stow and Link secure mount</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CPSC-certified</li>\n\n\n\n<li>three sizes (S 53-56cm, M 56-59cm &amp; L 59-62cm)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>claimed 420g (size M)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ride Concepts Deploy &amp; Dissent MTB helmets – Available Now!</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both new mountain bike helmets are in stock and <a href=\"https://rideconcepts.com/collections/helmets\" target=\"_blank\">available now online</a> directly from Ride Concepts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://rideconcepts.com/\" target=\"_blank\">RideConcepts.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/say-hello-to-the-deploy-and-dissent-ride-concepts-first-ever-mtb-helmets/\">Say Hello to the Deploy and Dissent, Ride Concepts’ First Ever MTB Helmets</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ff4bf6987abcab7f6bedc3f36c948f548443c69f959eee6e8635c2868860353b","category":"Cycling"}